+# OFARM plan drift check and continuation memo v0.1
+
+Date: 2026-04-12  
+Status: active supporting implementation artifact  
+Scope: re-read the hardest-design amendment plan, check post-wave concentration risk, and steer the next bounded continuation step back toward a central plan-linked seam
+
+---
+
+## Decision
+
+No active-law drift was found, but a process-level concentration risk did appear.
+
+The post-amendment support work had gone deeper into same-standard bridge rehearsal than into some central plan-linked rows around current-state explainability and authority depth.
+
+## Consequence
+
+The next bounded continuation should therefore:
+- stay in `04_implementation_and_conformance/`
+- avoid baseline/RFC changes
+- return to central hardest-design seams before any further bridge specialization
+
+Chosen continuation order:
+1. runtime-produced materialization freshness and basis-trace evidence
+2. deeper authority inheritance / revocation / non-human review evidence
+
+That is the continuation posture used in this package.
